# Bash Local
# This file is copied over ~/.bash_local and won't be tracked
# so you can activate specific config for a specific machine
# without having to commit and propagate this conf to other setups.

# iTerm2 SHELL INTEGRATION
# =========================
# This should come after prompt section because it modify it,
# it adds "marks" before the prompt to show that shell integration is available
#
# test -e "${HOME}/.iterm2_shell_integration.bash" && source "${HOME}/.iterm2_shell_integration.bash"

# 1 Navigate marks: Cmd-Shift-Up and Down-arrow keys.
# 2 Alert box when a mark appears (for long run tasks): Alert on next mark (Cmd-Opt-A)
# 3 Right-click on a mark to see it returning code (same line of the launched command)
# 4 imgls, imgcat, ectr: https://www.iterm2.com/documentation-shell-integration.html
